raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Functions as the Point of Contact (POC) to customers, project team, and stakeholders. Leads teams on large projects or significant segment of large complex projects.  In depth Understanding of the Systems Development Life Cycle (SDLC). Experience with Microsoft Office and project management related tools.  Knowledge of Project Management Methodologies (i.e., PMI PMBOK).  Plans, initiates, and manages information technology projects. Leads and guides the work of technical staff. Serves as liaison between business and technical aspects of projects. Plans project stages and assesses business implications for each stage. Monitors progress to assure deadlines, standards, and cost targets are met. May supervise others. Prepares long and short-range plans for application selection, systems development, systems maintenance, and production activities and for necessary support resources. Analyzes project related problems and creates solutions involving finance, scheduling, technology, methodology, and tools.
